00:35:57.154 --> 00:35:58.989
A super creepy one.

00:36:02.076 --> 00:36:04.662
Don't worry. It's never coming back.

00:36:12.252 --> 00:36:13.587
Friends...

00:36:27.601 --> 00:36:28.435
What?

00:36:29.645 --> 00:36:30.437
Why?

00:36:32.147 --> 00:36:33.941
There he is.

00:36:33.941 --> 00:36:35.234
Ishida!

00:36:35.818 --> 00:36:38.028
Look at this!

00:36:38.028 --> 00:36:40.614
This is your bike, right?

00:36:42.282 --> 00:36:44.076
Good timing!

00:36:44.785 --> 00:36:48.205
I'm glad it had your address on it.

00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:51.834
Where did you find it?

00:36:51.834 --> 00:36:53.669
Dumped in a paddy field.

00:36:54.086 --> 00:36:56.338
Man, I had to look everywhere.

00:36:56.714 --> 00:36:59.925
I'm glad I got it back for you, though.

00:37:07.182 --> 00:37:08.684
What's wrong, Ishida?

00:37:09.059 --> 00:37:10.769
Oh, uh...

00:37:12.062 --> 00:37:13.480
What's your name?

00:37:14.565 --> 00:37:15.858
I'm Nagatsuka.

00:37:16.483 --> 00:37:18.652
I sit behind you, you know.

00:37:20.070 --> 00:37:23.115
Oh, right. This is good bread.

00:37:23.115 --> 00:37:25.033
Want some, Nagatsuka?

00:37:25.284 --> 00:37:27.244
Ishida!

00:37:27.828 --> 00:37:28.787
Ishida!

00:37:30.456 --> 00:37:31.623
Morning.

00:37:33.041 --> 00:37:34.126
Morning.

00:37:36.462 --> 00:37:37.463
Ishida.

00:37:38.297 --> 00:37:40.215
Let's go hang out after school today.

00:37:40.507 --> 00:37:42.718
To mark the start of our friendship.

00:37:43.302 --> 00:37:45.721
Over here, Ishida.

00:38:08.660 --> 00:38:10.412
Is something wrong, Yasho?

00:38:12.247 --> 00:38:13.582
N-Nothing.

00:38:13.582 --> 00:38:15.000
Wait, Yasho?

00:38:15.000 --> 00:38:16.960
Makes us seem like big friends, right?

00:38:19.963 --> 00:38:22.007
And? Is something on your mind?

00:38:22.382 --> 00:38:24.051
Feel free to tell me.

00:38:24.051 --> 00:38:25.677
We're best friends.

00:38:30.057 --> 00:38:32.059
Say, Nagatsuka...

00:38:32.851 --> 00:38:35.604
What are friends, anyway?

00:38:36.313 --> 00:38:43.237
You know, does one need to fulfill
any requirements to be a friend?

00:38:44.446 --> 00:38:46.156
Look, Yasho.

00:38:49.535 --> 00:38:50.786
Hold out your hand.

00:39:04.466 --> 00:39:06.760
And that is what friends are.

00:39:06.760 --> 00:39:08.303
You see, Ishida...

00:39:09.096 --> 00:39:14.268
I think friendship defies logic or words.

00:39:14.560 --> 00:39:17.521
And requirements can kiss my ass.

00:39:17.980 --> 00:39:19.273
How stupid.

00:39:21.984 --> 00:39:22.776
She's not here.

00:39:23.694 --> 00:39:24.528
Uh, she's right there.

00:39:24.778 --> 00:39:25.696
She's not.

00:39:26.238 --> 00:39:28.740
Uh, who are?

00:39:28.740 --> 00:39:31.535
I'm Shoko's boyfriend.

00:39:32.661 --> 00:39:35.038
Well, that sucks.

00:39:35.038 --> 00:39:37.791
For the bread, not me.

00:39:38.208 --> 00:39:40.586
So, huh...

00:39:40.586 --> 00:39:42.713
Nishimiya likes younger boys?

00:39:42.713 --> 00:39:44.631
Wow, that's kinda unexpected.

00:39:45.549 --> 00:39:47.759
Here, take the bread, at least.

00:39:47.759 --> 00:39:48.594
It's good bread.

00:39:48.594 --> 00:39:49.052
Look.

00:39:49.678 --> 00:39:53.682
If you're here just to make yourself
feel better, please leave.

00:39:57.561 --> 00:39:59.146
Are we done here?

00:39:59.938 --> 00:40:00.606
Goodbye.

00:40:01.940 --> 00:40:03.442
Hey, laddy!

00:40:03.442 --> 00:40:06.570
My bud says he wants to see Nishimiya!

00:40:06.570 --> 00:40:07.404
Nagatsuka?

00:40:07.404 --> 00:40:09.781
Quit being an ass and bring her out!

00:40:09.781 --> 00:40:12.034
What are you doing here?

00:40:12.951 --> 00:40:13.994
I followed you.

00:40:13.994 --> 00:40:15.746
That's what best friends do, right?

00:40:16.663 --> 00:40:19.458
I guess turds of a feather drop together.

00:40:19.458 --> 00:40:21.084
Shithead.

00:40:22.002 --> 00:40:24.254
